-- Schlecker Fate Rests With Allianz’s Euler Hermes Unit, FTD Says
-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 2012-05-29T06:00:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-29/schlecker-fate-rests-with-allianz-s-euler-hermes-unit-ftd-says.html
German retail chain Schlecker’s
future may depend on  Allianz SE (ALV) ’s Euler Hermes unit, which
insured 300 million euros ($376 million) of unpaid deliveries,
Financial Times Deutschland  reported , citing Arndt Geiwitz,
Schlecker’s insolvency administrator.  Prospective buyers have until June 1 to make an offer for
Schlecker, FTD cited Geiwitz as saying. If none is received, he
will shut the company, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Webb in Frankfurt at 
